				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12134749/scp-1767#post-4289507</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 24 Jun 2019 04:45:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Yiwmiy Yyy</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5238698</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Judy just <em>had</em> to leave&#8230;.</p> <p>I think this is a good page, mainly because it tells a story from the point of view from the &quot;lab rat&quot; itself, not the scientists . It shows what it is feeling as the experiment just goes deeper, and darker.</p> <p>Just one thing: The caption for the photo says SCP-1712, not 1767. That's all.</p> <p>In the end, I really did enjoy reading this page, as it showed a more different main point of view than other pages I've read.</p> <p>Wait, it's 12 AM Eastern Time already? It's only 9 PM for me! This is why I don't always like living in the Pacific Time Zone.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
